{"title_page": "Les Petits Meurtres d'Agatha Christie", "text_new": "{{short description|French TV detective series 2006, 2009\u20132019}}\n{{EngvarB|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = {{lang|fr|Les Petits Meurtres d'Agatha Christie}}\n| image                    = Les Petits Meurtres d'Agatha Christie.png\n| genre                    = [[Police procedural]]\n| creator                  = Anne Giafferi <br/> [[Murielle Magellan]]\n| writer                   = \n| director                 = \n| starring                 = ''Series One'':<br/>\n[[Antoine Dul\u00e9ry]]<br/>\n[[Marius Colucci]]<br/>\n''Series Two'':<br/>\n[[Samuel Labarthe]]<br/>\n[[Blandine Bellavoir]]<br/>\n[[\u00c9lodie Frenck]]<br/>\n| composer                 = \n| country                  = France\n| location                 = France\n| language                 = French\n| num_series               = 2\n| num_episodes             = 11 {{!}} 27\n| list_episodes            = \n| executive_producer       = \n| company                  = Escazai Films\n| distributor              = FranceTv, RLJ-Acorn (DVD), MHZ (USTV) (DVD)\n| camera                   = \n| runtime                  = 100 minutes\n| network                  = [[France 2]]\n| picture_format           = [[480i]] ([[Standard-definition television|SDTV]]) <br> [[720p]] ([[High-definition television|HDTV]])\n| first_aired              = 9 January 2009\n| last_aired               = present<ref name=\"telestar\" />\n| website                  = http://www.france2.fr/emissions/les-petits-meurtres-d-agatha-christie\n| show_name_2              = The Little Murders of Agatha Christie; Agatha Christie's Criminal Games\n| based_on                 = [[Agatha Christie]]'s detective fiction\n| preceded_by              = {{lang|fr|Petits Meurtres en Famille}} 2006 (4-part mini-series)\n}}\n'''{{lang|fr|Les Petits Meurtres d'Agatha Christie}}''' (English title: \"'''''The Little Murders of Agatha Christie'''''\") is a French-language, [[Police procedural|police procedural genre]] television program consisting of two series loosely based on [[Agatha Christie|Agatha Christie's]] works of detective fiction. First broadcast on [[France 2]] on 9 January [[2009 in television|2009]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.agathachristie.com/film-and-tv/les-petits-meurtres-dagatha-christie|title=Les Petits Meurtres d'Agatha Christie|last=|first=|date=2020|website=The Home of Agatha Christie|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=13 April 2020}}</ref> Series One takes place in 1930s France with {{lang|fr|Commissaire}} (approximately [[Chief inspector#United%20Kingdom|DCI]]) Larosi\u00e8re ([[Antoine Dul\u00e9ry]]) and {{Lang|fr|Inspecteur}} Lampion ([[Marius Colucci]]). Series Two is set in mid-1950s through 1960s France with Commissaire Laurence ([[Samuel Labarthe]]), his secretary Marl\u00e8ne Leroy ([[\u00c9lodie Frenck]]), and newspaper reporter Alice Avril ([[Blandine Bellavoir]]). In English-speaking countries, the second series is titled \"Agatha Christie's Criminal Games\" and has streamed on [[MHz Choice]] in the United States and [[Special Broadcasting Service|SBS]] in Australia.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://watch.mhzchoice.com/agatha-christie-s-criminal-games|title=Agatha Christie's Criminal Games|website=MHz Choice|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref><ref> {{Cite web|url=https://www.sbs.com.au/ondemand/program/agatha-christies-criminal-games|title=Agatha Christie's Criminal Games|last=|first=|date=|website=SBS On Demand|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref> The thirty-eight episodes to the end of Series Two include adaptations of thirty-six of Christie's works.\n\nA third series, with a new cast and set in 1970s France, was announced in 2019.<ref name=\"telestar\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.telestar.fr/actu-tv/exclu-telestar-les-petits-meurtres-d-agatha-christie-ce-n-est-pas-fini-467484|title=EXCLU TELESTAR. Les Petits meurtres d'Agatha Christie ce n'est... - T\u00e9l\u00e9 Star|last=Telestar.fr|date=2019-10-28|website=www.telestar.fr|language=fr|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n\n==Series One: 1930s France (2009\u20132012)==\n\n=== Overview ===\nIn France in the 1930s, ladies' man Commissaire Jean Larosi\u00e8re and his hapless junior officer Inspecteur \u00c9mile Lampion unravel a series of complicated murder cases to reveal the killers.  \n\n=== Cast and Characters ===\n==== Main ====\n* [[Antoine Dul\u00e9ry]] as Commissaire Jean Larosi\u00e8re (11 episodes)\n* [[Marius Colucci]] as Inspecteur \u00c9mile Lampion (11 episodes)\n\n==== Recurring ====\n* [[Serge Dubois]] as M\u00e9nard (8 episodes)\n* [[Olivier Carr\u00e9 (acteur)|Olivier Carr\u00e9]] as Verdure (5 episodes)\n\n=== Episodes ===\n<!-- For help with these templates see \nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Template:Episode_table\nhttp://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Template:Episode_list -->\n\n{{Episode table|background=|total_width=75|series=|title=25|aux1=25|aux1T=Christie adaptation|DirectedBy=25|airdate=10|episodes=\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber  = 1\n |Title           = {{lang|fr|Les meurtres ABC}}\n |Aux1            = [[The A.B.C. Murders]]\n |DirectedBy      = [[Eric Woreth]]\n |OriginalAirDate = 2009\n |ShortSummary    = As a serial killer taunts Larosi\u00e8re, the great detective's career could be the next casualty.\n |LineColor       = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber  = 2\n |Title           = {{lang|fr|Am stram gram}}\n |Aux1            = [[Ordeal by Innocence]]\n |DirectedBy      = [[St\u00e9phane Kappes]]\n |OriginalAirDate = 2009\n |ShortSummary    = After the death of a beloved philanthropist, suspicion falls on her brood of adopted children.\n |LineColor       = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber  = 3\n |Title           = {{lang|fr|La plume empoisonn\u00e9e}}\n |Aux1            = [[The Moving Finger]]\n |DirectedBy      = Eric Woreth\n |OriginalAirDate = 2009\n |ShortSummary    = Lampion gets badly wounded during a case and has to rest. Larosi\u00e8re rents a room for him in a small village which looks the perfect place to recover, except someone is sending ugly poison-pen letters.\n |LineColor       = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber  = 4\n |Title           = {{lang|fr|La maison du p\u00e9ril}}\n |Aux1            = [[Peril at End House]]\n |DirectedBy      = Eric Woreth\n |OriginalAirDate = 2009\n |ShortSummary    = When a beautiful heiress is targeted for murder, Larosi\u00e8re loses his heart and nearly his life.\n |LineColor       = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber  = 5\n |Title           = {{lang|fr|Le chat et les souris}}\n |Aux1            = [[Cat Among the Pigeons]]\n |DirectedBy      = Eric Woreth\n |OriginalAirDate = 2010\n |ShortSummary    = While investigating murders at a boarding school, Larosi\u00e8re is haunted by his past.\n |LineColor       = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber  = 6\n |Title           = {{lang|fr|Je ne suis pas coupable}}\n |Aux1            = [[Sad Cypress]]\n |DirectedBy      = Eric Woreth\n |OriginalAirDate = 2010\n |ShortSummary    = When death stalks a women's retreat, a reluctant Lampion goes undercover.\n |LineColor       = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber  = 7\n |Title           = {{lang|fr|Cinq petits cochons}}\n |Aux1            = [[Five Little Pigs]]\n |DirectedBy      = Eric Woreth\n |OriginalAirDate = 2011\n |ShortSummary    = Investigating a fifteen year old cold case, Larosi\u00e8re confronts five suspects with contradictory testimonies. <!-- revised -->\n |LineColor       = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber  = 8\n |Title           = {{lang|fr|Le flux et le reflux}}\n |Aux1            = [[Taken at the Flood]]\n |DirectedBy      = Eric Woreth\n |OriginalAirDate = 2011\n |ShortSummary    = Larosi\u00e8re runs into his former captain from the Great War, who invites him to his family castle and surprises everyone when he{{Whose|date=April 2020}} announces his marriage to Albertine, a young woman he met in Africa.\n |LineColor       = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber  = 9\n |Title           = {{lang|fr|Un cadavre sur l'oreiller}}\n |Aux1            = [[The Body in the Library]]\n |DirectedBy      = Eric Woreth\n |OriginalAirDate = 2011\n |ShortSummary    = With Larosi\u00e8re accused of strangling a prostitute, Lampion tries to clear his{{Whose|date=April 2020}} name.\n |LineColor       = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber  = 10\n |Title           = {{lang|fr|Un meurtre en sommeil}}\n |Aux1            = [[Sleeping Murder]]\n |DirectedBy      = Eric Woreth\n |OriginalAirDate = 2012\n |ShortSummary    = Sacha escapes from a psychiatric hospital and hides in an isolated house. On the first evening, she has a vision of a bloody woman. Is it related to a recently deceased woman in a house nearby?\n |LineColor       = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber  = 11\n |Title           = {{lang|fr|Le couteau sur la nuque}}\n |Aux1            = [[Lord Edgware Dies]]\n |DirectedBy      = [[Renaud Bertrand]]\n |OriginalAirDate = 2012\n |ShortSummary    = The Larosi\u00e8re/Lampion duo investigate the murder of a woman last seen entering a theatre. Meanwhile, the commissaire's daughter, Juliette, storms into his life and might be in danger.\n |LineColor       = \n}}\n}}\n\n== Series Two: mid-1950s to 1960s France (2013\u20132020) ==\n\n=== Overview ===\nThe action has moved to mid-1950s to 1960s [[Lille]], France. Suave and razor-sharp, Commissaire Swan Laurence investigates murders with the often unappreciated assistance of reporter Alice Avril and police secretary Marl\u00e8ne Leroy. \u00a0\n\n=== Cast and Characters ===\n==== Main ====\n* [[Samuel Labarthe]] as Commissaire Swan Laurence (27 episodes)<ref> {{Cite web|url=https://www.agathachristie.com/film-and-tv/les-petits-meurtres-dagatha-christie/meet-the-characters/samuel-labarthe|title=Samuel Labarthe|last=|first=|date=|website=The Home of Agatha Christie|language=en-US|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-13}} </ref>\n* [[Blandine Bellavoir]] as journalist Alice Avril (27 episodes)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.agathachristie.com/film-and-tv/les-petits-meurtres-dagatha-christie/meet-the-characters/blandine-bellavoir|title=Blandine Bellavoir|website=www.agathachristie.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref>\n* [[\u00c9lodie Frenck]] as police secretary Marl\u00e8ne Leroy (27 episodes)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.agathachristie.com/film-and-tv/les-petits-meurtres-dagatha-christie/meet-the-characters/\u00e9lodie-frenck|title=\u00c9lodie Frenck|website=www.agathachristie.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref>\n\n==== Recurring ====\n* [[Dominique Thomas]] as Ernest Tricard (27 episodes)\n* [[Christophe Piret]] / [[Fran\u00e7ois Godart]] as Robert Jourdeuil (2 / 15 episodes)\n* [[Cyril Guei]] as Dr Timoth\u00e9e Glissant (13 episodes)\n* [[Marie Berto]] as Arlette Carmouille (5 episodes)\n* [[Natacha Lindinger]] as Euphrasie Maillol (4 episodes)\n* [[Antoine Dul\u00e9ry]] as Commissaire Larosi\u00e8re's nephew (1 episode, see Series One)\n\n=== Episodes ===\n<!-- For help with these templates see \nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Template:Episode_table\nhttp://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Template:Episode_list -->\n\n{{Episode table|background=|total_width=75|series=|title=25|aux1=25|aux1T=Christie adaptation|DirectedBy=25|airdate=10|episodes=\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber  = 1\n |Title           = {{lang|fr|Jeux de glaces}}\n |Aux1            = [[They Do It With Mirrors]]\n |DirectedBy      = [[Eric Woreth]]\n |OriginalAirDate = 2013\n |ShortSummary    = Laurence investigates gruesome murders in a rehabilitation centre.\n |LineColor       = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber  = 2\n |Title           = {{lang|fr|Meurtre au champagne}}\n |Aux1            = [[Sparkling Cyanide]]\n |DirectedBy      = Eric Woreth\n |OriginalAirDate = 2013\n |ShortSummary    = A famous movie star commits suicide during the shooting of her latest film. Alice replaces her on the set while Laurence investigates.\n |LineColor       = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber  = 3\n |Title           = {{lang|fr|T\u00e9moin Muet}}\n |Aux1            = [[Dumb Witness]]\n |DirectedBy      = [[Marc Angelo]]\n |OriginalAirDate = 2013\n |ShortSummary    = A rich woman and her maid are found murdered in an old castle. The only witnesses are a dog and ghosts which seem prone to reveal the truth. Fascinated by divination, the Laurence's mother fully intends to participate in her son's investigation.\n |LineColor       = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber  = 4\n |Title           = {{lang|fr|Pourquoi pas Martin?}}\n |Aux1            = [[Why Didn't They Ask Evans?]]\n |DirectedBy      = Marc Angelo\n |OriginalAirDate = 2013\n |ShortSummary    = Avril comes to a dying man's rescue on a cliff. While she hears his last words, she notices a woman's portrait next to him. She seeks help at the village, but when she returns, the photo is missing.\n |LineColor       = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber  = 5\n |Title           = {{lang|fr|Meurtre \u00e0 la kermesse}}\n |Aux1            = [[Hallowe'en Party]]\n |DirectedBy      = Eric Woreth\n |OriginalAirDate = 2014\n |ShortSummary    = After a gunfight, Laurence is left blind. Meanwhile a child is found drowned in a bucket of water. Laurence decides to hide his condition to investigate with Avril, who becomes his eyes.\n |LineColor       = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber  = 6\n |Title           = {{lang|fr|Cartes sur table}}\n |Aux1            = [[Cards on the Table]]\n |DirectedBy      = Eric Woreth\n |OriginalAirDate = 2014\n |ShortSummary    = A strange, wealthy man induces a dubious Laurence and Avril to attend a dinner party he is hosting with four other guests whom he suggests got away with murder, plus a self-proclaimed former member of France's secret service. When the host is murdered at the party, Laurence investigates.  Two guests are subsequently murdered and Laurence himself becomes a suspect before determining the culprit. <!-- revised -->\n |LineColor       = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber  = 7\n |Title           = {{lang|fr|Le crime ne paie pas}}\n |Aux1            = [[Murder on the Links]]\n |DirectedBy      = Marc Angelo\n |OriginalAirDate = 2014\n |ShortSummary    = Avril goes undercover in a cabaret where a waitress was killed and the boss kidnapped. Laurence has to deal with an officer from the \"police of the police\" who wants him removed from the investigation.\n |LineColor       = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber  = 8\n |Title           = {{lang|fr|Pension Vanilos}}\n |Aux1            = [[Hickory Dickory Dock]]\n |DirectedBy      = Eric Woreth\n |OriginalAirDate = 2015\n |ShortSummary    = Marl\u00e8ne asks for Laurence's help on a case involving her sister Solange, who runs a boarding house  where a young woman dropped dead of poisoning.\n |LineColor       = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber  = 9\n |Title           = {{lang|fr|Un meurtre est-il facile?}}\n |Aux1            = [[Murder is Easy]]\n |DirectedBy      = Marc Angelo\n |OriginalAirDate = 2015\n |ShortSummary    = Avril receives a marriage proposal from Emile Deboucke, an older rich spinning mills owner.  Her engagement is not a bed of roses and soon she has to deal with a series of murders.\n |LineColor       = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber  = 10\n |Title           = {{lang|fr|Madame Mac Ginty est morte}}\n |Aux1            = [[Mrs McGinty's Dead]]\n |DirectedBy      = [[Didier Bivel]], Eric Woreth\n |OriginalAirDate = 2015\n |ShortSummary    = Avril's ex-husband is accused of murder. She discovers him hiding in her apartment and does not turn him to the police.\n |LineColor       = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber  = 11\n |Title           = {{lang|fr|Murder Party}}\n |Aux1            = [[A Murder is Announced]]\n |DirectedBy      = Eric Woreth\n |OriginalAirDate = 2015\n |ShortSummary    = Marl\u00e8ne is puzzled by an advertisement in the paper for a \"murder party\". Laurence believes it is a joke, but at set time a man interrupts the party violently and drops dead.\n |LineColor       = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber  = 12\n |Title           = {{lang|fr|L'\u00e9trange enl\u00e8vement du petit Bruno}}\n |Aux1            = [[The Adventure of Johnnie Waverly]]\n |DirectedBy      = Eric Woreth\n |OriginalAirDate = 2016\n |ShortSummary    = Laurence has died on duty. Eight days earlier, he was called to protect the son of famous novelist Elo\u00efse Zennefort.\n |LineColor       = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber  = 13\n |Title           = {{lang|fr|Le cheval p\u00e2le}}\n |Aux1            = [[The Pale Horse]]\n |DirectedBy      = [[Olivier Panchot]]\n |OriginalAirDate = 2016\n |ShortSummary    = Laurence investigates whether the death of Alice's young heiress friend is related to  occult powers.\n |LineColor       = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber  = 14\n |Title           = {{lang|fr|L'affaire Protheroe}}\n |Aux1            = [[The Murder at the Vicarage]]\n |DirectedBy      = Olivier Panchot\n |OriginalAirDate = 2016\n |ShortSummary    = After a young secretary hangs herself, Laurence suspects sinister forces led to her death.\n |LineColor       = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber  = 15\n |Title           = {{lang|fr|La myst\u00e9rieuse affaire de Styles}}\n |Aux1            = [[The Mysterious Affair at Styles]]\n |DirectedBy      = Eric Woreth\n |OriginalAirDate = 2016\n |ShortSummary    = Laurence and Avril investigate a wealthy spa owner after a man drowns in her establishment.\n |LineColor       = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber  = 16\n |Title           = {{lang|fr|Albert Major parlait trop}}\n |Aux1            = [[A Caribbean Mystery]]\n |DirectedBy      = Eric Woreth\n |OriginalAirDate = 2016\n |ShortSummary    = Avril investigates a murder in a hospital while she's admitted for her own injuries.\n |LineColor       = \n}}