 Tragedy]]\n |DirectedBy      = Nicolas Picard-Dreyfuss\n |OriginalAirDate = 2018\n |ShortSummary    = Murder befalls Alice's acting class, which features a guest teacher who looks exactly like Laurence.\n |LineColor       = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber  = 22\n |Title           = {{lang|fr|Meurtres en solde}}\n |Aux1            = [[Hercule Poirot's Christmas]]\n |DirectedBy      = [[Didier Bivel]]\n |OriginalAirDate = 2018\n |ShortSummary    = Avril is attacked and struggles with amnesia while working on an article. The bodies of a man and a woman are found at a car crash and the deaths look suspicious. (This adaptation has no Christmas theme.)\n |LineColor       = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber  = 23\n |Title           = {{lang|fr|M\u00e9lodie Mortelle}}\n |Aux1            = [[The Sittaford Mystery]]\n |DirectedBy      = [[Christophe Campos]]\n |OriginalAirDate = 2018\n |ShortSummary    = &nbsp;\n |LineColor       = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber  = 24\n |Title           = {{lang|fr|Ding Dingue Dong}}\n |Aux1            = [[Evil Under the Sun]]\n |DirectedBy      = Christophe Campos\n |OriginalAirDate = 2019\n |ShortSummary    = &nbsp;\n |LineColor       = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber  = 25\n |Title           = {{lang|fr|L'Heure Zero}}\n |Aux1            = [[Towards Zero]]\n |DirectedBy      = Nicolas Picard-Dreyfuss\n |OriginalAirDate = 2019\n |ShortSummary    = &nbsp;\n |LineColor       = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber  = 26\n |Title           = {{lang|fr|Rendez-vous avec la Mort}}\n |Aux1            = [[Appointment with Death]]\n |DirectedBy      = Nicolas Picard-Dreyfuss\n |OriginalAirDate = 2019\n |ShortSummary    = &nbsp;\n |LineColor       = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber  = 27\n |Title           = {{lang|fr|Un Cadavre au Petit D\u00e9jeuner}}\n |Aux1            = not adapted\n |DirectedBy      = Nicolas Picard-Dreyfuss\n |OriginalAirDate = 2019/2020\n |ShortSummary    = (Original musical-comedy episode;<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sbs.com.au/ondemand/video/1676468291833/agatha-christies-criminal-games-a-body-with-breakfast|title=Agatha Christie's Criminal Games: A Body with Breakfast|last=|first=|date=|website=SBS On Demand|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-15}}</ref> first aired in Italy in 2019, Australia in 2020, and in France expected late 2020.)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mondofox.it/guida-tv/foxcrime/2019-10-31/|title=GUIDA TV di FoxCrime di gioved\u00ec 31 ottobre 2019|last=|first=|date=31 October 2019|website=MondoFox|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=14 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|title=\"Les petits meurtres d'Agatha Christie\" Un cadavre au petit d\u00e9jeuner (TV Episode 2019) - IMDb|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt10269126/releaseinfo|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref><ref name=\"telestar\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.telestar.fr/actu-tv/exclu-telestar-les-petits-meurtres-d-agatha-christie-ce-n-est-pas-fini-467484|title=EXCLU TELESTAR. Les Petits meurtres d'Agatha Christie ce n'est... - T\u00e9l\u00e9 Star|last=Telestar.fr|date=2019-10-28|website=www.telestar.fr|language=fr|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n |LineColor       = \n}}\n}}\n\n== Series Three: 1970s France (announced 2019) ==\nA third series, with a new cast and set in France in the 1970s, was announced in 2019. The first episode is expected to be released in late 2020.<ref name=\"telestar\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.programme.tv/news/series/208867-emotion-dans-greys-anatomy-la-nouvelle-saison-des-petits-meurtres-dagatha-christie-et-les-abdos-de-loup-denis-elion-les-tournages-de-la-semaine-photos/|title=Emotion dans Grey\u2019s Anatomy, la nouvelle saison des Petits Meurtres d\u2019Agatha Christie et les abdos de Loup-Denis Elion\u2026 Les tournages de la semaine (PHOTOS) - series - T\u00e9l\u00e9 2 semaines|website=www.programme.tv/news|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n\n== Complete Cast ==\n{| class=\"wikitable mw-collapsible mw-collapsed center\" style=\"font-size: 86%; width:60%; left:0 auto; text-align:center;\"\n|+ align=\"center\" colspan=\"4\" |<big>{{nowrap|Cast of Series One and Series Two}}</big>\n|- style=\"background-color: #CCCCFF\" \n|'''Casting'''||'''Character'''||'''Episodes'''|| scope=\"col\" style=\"width: 80px;\" |'''Year'''\n|-\n|[[Antoine Dul\u00e9ry]]\n|Jean Larosi\u00e8re<br />Larosi\u00e8re's nephew\n|11<br />1\n|2009\u20132012&nbsp;<br />2020\n|-\n|[[Marius Colucci]]\n|\u00c9mile Lampion\n|11\n|2009\u20132012\n|-\n|[[Blandine Bellavoir]]\n|Alice Avril\n|27\n|2013\u20132020\n|-\n|[[Samuel Labarthe]]\n|Swan Laurence\n|27\n|2013\u20132020\n|-\n|[[\u00c9lodie Frenck]]\n|Marl\u00e8ne Leroy\n|27\n|2013\u20132020\n|-\n|[[Dominique Thomas]]\n|Ernest Tricard\n|27\n|2013\u20132020\n|-\n|[[Christophe Piret]]\n|Guillaume Parisot<br />Robert Jourdeuil\n|1<br />2\n|2012<br />2013\n|-\n|[[Fran\u00e7ois Godart]]\n|Robert Jourdeuil\n|15\n|2013\u20132019\n|-\n|[[Serge Dubois]]\n|M\u00e9nard\n|8\n|2009\u20132012\n|-\n|[[Olivier Carr\u00e9 (acteur)|Olivier Carr\u00e9]]\n|Verdure<br />Roger Bessan\n|5<br />1\n|2010\u20132012<br />2019\n|-\n|[[Flore Bonaventura]]<br />[[Alice Isaaz]]\n|Juliette Larosi\u00e8re\n|1<br />1\n|2010<br />2012\n|-\n|[[Anne Beno\u00eet]]\n|Madame Daste<br />Annick Devassene\n|1<br />1\n|2009<br />2015\n|-\n|[[H\u00e9l\u00e8ne Vincent]]\n|Kristin\n|1\n|2009\n|-\n|[[Pascal Elso]]\n|L\u00e9opold Vallabr\u00e8gues\n|1\n|2009\n|-\n|[[Corinne Masiero]]\n|Ang\u00e9lique\n|1\n|2009\n|-\n|[[Denis Lavant]]\n|Andr\u00e9 Custe\n|1\n|2009\n|-\n|[[Fr\u00e9d\u00e9ric Pierrot]]\n|Jean Villiers\n|1\n|2009\n|-\n|[[Robinson St\u00e9venin]]\n|Jean\n|1\n|2009\n|-\n|[[Fran\u00e7oise Bertin]]\n|Emilie Dubreuil\n|1\n|2009\n|-\n|[[Lannick Gautry]]\n|Mathieu Vidal\n|1\n|2010\n|-\n|[[Isabelle Candelier]]\n|Christine Boisseau\n|1\n|2010\n|-\n|[[Guilaine Londez]]\n|Mademoiselle Thuleau\n|1\n|2010\n|-\n|[[Mata Gabin]]\n|Esm\u00e9ralda\n|1\n|2011\n|-\n|[[Jean-Marie Winling]]\n|Pierre Foug\u00e8res\n|1\n|2012\n|-\n|[[Patrick Descamps]]\n|Chesnais\n|1\n|2012\n|-\n|[[Fran\u00e7oise Fabian]]\n|Alexina Laurence\n|1\n|2013\n|-\n|[[Claude Perron]]\n|Claude Kerrigan\n|1\n|2013\n|-\n|[[Charlie Dupont]]\n|Roland Delavall\u00e9e\n|1\n|2013\n|-\n|[[Isabelle de Hertogh]]\n|Bella Siatidis\n|1\n|2013\n|-\n|[[Dominique Pinon]]\n|Hubert Petitpont\n|1\n|2014\n|-\n|[[Natacha Lindinger]]\n|Euphrasie Maillol\n|4\n|2014\n|-\n|[[Nicolas Vaude]]\n|Stanislas\n|1\n|2014\n|-\n|[[Alban Lenoir]]\n|Paul Coupet\n|1\n|2014\n|-\n|[[Philippe Nahon]]\n|Emile Deboucke\n|1\n|2015\n|-\n|[[Serge Riaboukine]]\n|L\u00e9opold Santini\n|1\n|2015\n|-\n|[[Cyril Guei]]\n|Dr Timoth\u00e9e Glissant\n|13\n|2016\u20132020\n|-\n|[[Sophie Cattani]]\n|Eve Constantin\n|1\n|2016\n|-\n|[[Philippe Rebbot]]\n|Dr Locart\n|1\n|2018\n|-\n|[[Marie Berto]]\n|Arlette Carmouille\n|5\n|2016\u20132020\n|- \n|[[Barbara Schulz]]\n|Audrey Fontaine\n|1\n|2019\n|-\n|[[Nuno Lopes]]\n|Maxime Beaumont\n|1\n|2019\n|-\n|[[Mireille Herbstmeyer]]\n|Cl\u00e9mence Berg\n|1\n|2019\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of French television series]]\n\n==Trivia==\n* In the second season of the French TV series \"{{lang|fr|Les Petits Meurtres d'Agatha Christie}}\", Commissaire Swan Laurence drives a [[Facel Vega]] Facellia FA red Bordeaux coupe.<ref>{{cite web|title=V\u00e9hicule du film \"les petits meurtres d'Agatha Christie\"|periodical=|publisher=|url=https://www.lesanciennes.com/annonce/A312537-ventes-auto-facel-vega-facellia-fa-coupe-2-2-1960.html?ftype=&fcat=&search=FACEL%20VEGA|url-status=|format=|access-date=2020-04-09|archive-url=|archive-date=|last=|date=2020-03-08|year=|language=|pages=|quote=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Facel Vega \u00e1 la T\u00e9l\u00e9vision|periodical=|publisher=|url=http://www.facel-vega.asso.fr/tv/tv.html|url-status=|format=|access-date=2020-04-09|archive-url=|archive-date=|last=|date=2013-03-29|year=|language=|pages=|quote=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=RR Forums Australia|periodical=|publisher=|url=http://au.rrforums.net/forum/messages/16947/22770.html?1479246125|url-status=|format=|access-date=2020-04-09|archive-url=|archive-date=|last=|date=2016-11-15|year=|language=|pages=|quote=}}</ref>\n\n== 2006 mini-series ==\nA distinct four-part mini-series, \"{{lang|fr|Petits Meurtres en Famille}}\", adapted from ''[[Hercule Poirot's Christmas]]'', was released in 2006. Although Larosi\u00e8re and Lampion are the main characters (played by the same actors), this mini-series is not a prequel or sequel to the later series.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|id=1349600|title=Les Petits Meurtres d'Agatha Christie}}\n\n{{Television needs character section}}\n{{Television needs production section}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Petits Meurtres d'Agatha Christie}}\n[[Category:2009 French television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2000s French television series]]\n[[Category:2010s French television series]]\n[[Category:French crime television series]]\n[[Category:French-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Television programmes based on works by Agatha Christie]]\n", "name_user": "RLO1729", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eOverview:added forenames for consistency", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Les_Petits_Meurtres_d%27Agatha_Christie"}
{"title_page": "Kike Santander", "text_new": "{{Spanish name|Santander|Lora}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2019}}\n{{Infobox musical artist  <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject Musicians -->\n| name = Kike Santander\n| image = Kike Santander en Eurovisi\u00f3n 2004.jpg\n| caption = \n| image_size = \n| background          =  non_performing_personnel\n| birth_name          = Flavio Enrique Santander Lora\n| alias               = \n| birth_date=\n| birth_place=[[Santiago de Cali]], [[Colombia]]\n| death_date=\n| death_place=\n| occupation          = Composer and producer\n| years_active        = 1987\u2013present\n| Label              \n| Associated_a\n\n| label = Santander Records\n| website                 = [http://kikesantander.com/ KikeSantander.com] \u2013 official site in Spanish and English\n}}\n\n'''Flavio Enrique \"Kike\" Santander Lora''' is a [[Colombian Americans|Colombian-American]] composer, record producer, arranger and entrepreneur.<ref name=\"homenage\"/> He is considered to be one of the principal Latino composers of the day, having worked with artists such as [[David Bisbal]], [[Cristian Castro]], [[Thal\u00eda]], [[Chayanne]], [[Diego Torres (singer)|Diego Torres]], [[Davi Wornel]], [[Alejandro Fern\u00e1ndez]], [[Olga Ta\u00f1\u00f3n]], [[Bacilos]], [[Jos\u00e9 Luis Rodr\u00edguez (singer)|Jos\u00e9 Luis Rodr\u00edguez \u00abEl Puma\u00bb]] and [[Gloria Estefan]] among others.<ref name=\"KSMPM\">{{cite news|date=February 27, 2008 |url=http://www.revistadiners.com.co/noticia.php3?nt=23098 |title=Diners Journal:: The Magazine of the Month. Mi primer mill\u00f3n (Diners Journal: Journal of Mes. The first million) |language=Spanish |author=Constanza Morales Arias |accessdate=December 20, 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20040107043258/http://www.revistadiners.com.co/noticia.php3?nt=23098 |archivedate= January 7, 2004 }}</ref> Santander has composed more than 710 songs and has sold over 25 million albums worldwide.<ref name=\"homenage\">[http://50.22.195.205/noticia-670817.html?intId=670817 La Vanguardia: Kike Santander recibir\u00e1 homenaje en Las Vegas] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131110035848/http://50.22.195.205/noticia-670817.html?intId=670817 |date=November 10, 2013 }}  (in Spanish: Kike Santander will receive homage in Las Vegas). Posted in Thursday, March 10, 2011. Retrieved November 10, 2013, to 2:51pm.</ref> His work as songwriter and producer includes themes such as ''[[Let's Get Loud (Jennifer Lopez song)|Let's Get Loud]]'' by [[Jennifer Lopez]], ''[[Abriendo puertas (song)|Abriendo puertas]]'' by Gloria Estefan, ''[[Me Estoy Enamorando (album)|Me Estoy Enamorando]]'' by Alejandro Fern\u00e1ndez, ''[[Mi Vida Sin Tu Amor]]'' by Cristian Castro, and ''[[Premonici\u00f3n]]'' by David Bisbal, as well as many songs recorded by artists such as Thal\u00eda, [[Natalia Oreiro]], [[Gisselle]], [[Edith M\u00e1rquez]], [[Luis Miguel]], [[Soledad Pastorutti]] and the Spanish song for [[Eurovision Song Contest 2004]], amongst others.\n\nMore than 25 of his songs have been in the coveted Top Ten, as reflected in the Latin ''Billboard'' charts since 1999. More than 15 of his songs are featured within the top 100 played songs by the BMI Association of Authors and Composers. His songs and productions have surpassed 25 million albums worldwide <ref name=\"KSMPM\"/> and he has won prizes and awards that are given in the music industry on multiple occasions: [[Grammy Awards]], [[Billboard Music Award|Billboard]], [[Lo Nuestro Awards]], [[Premios TVyNovelas]], El Heraldo, and [[Broadcast Music Incorporated|BMI]] in which he has received the most awards in its Latin division, and many more.<ref name=\"GRESKI\"/> His brother is the composer [[Gustavo Santander]].\n\n== Early years ==\nKike Santander was born in [[Santiago de Cali]], [[Colombia]], and he was raised in La Flora, a typical upper-middle-class neighborhood of Cali. His father was the dentist, poet and guitarist Flavio Santander and his mother's name is Judith. His brother is the composer [[Gustavo Santander]]. In Cali he spent his first years learning different rhythms and musical skills while studying at Colegio Berchmans from which he graduated in 1977. He began his musical studies at an early age, playing the accordion (his first instrument, which he played since age 8) and experimenting with instruments like acoustic guitar (to age 12), electric guitar (to age 13), lira, the electric bass (to age 16), piano and later devoted himself to the percussion (to age 18).<ref name=\"abc\">[http://www.abc.com.py/nota/kike-santander-me-siento-mitad-paraguayo/ Digital ABC: Kike Santander: \u201cMe siento mitad paraguayo\u201d] (In Spanish: Kike Santander: \"I feel that am half Paraguayan\"). Published January 6, 2012, to 19:00 pm. Retrieved March 15, 2011, to 23:21 pm.</ref> His earliest musical influences came from a wide mix of genres that include indigenous artists of his native country. His main influences were [[bolero]], [[rock and roll]], Anglo-American [[pop music|pop]], [[classical music]] and [[jazz]]. He studied music at the Cali Conservatory. In 1978, when he was 18, he began his medical studies at the [[University of Valle]] from which he graduated in Medicine and Surgery.<ref name=\"GRESKI\"/> He worked as a doctor for one year before deciding to dedicate himself completely to studying music and his musical career.<ref name=\"abc\"/><ref name=\"GRESKI\">{{cite news|date=February 27, 2008 |url=http://www.grandesestrellas.com/k/kike-santander-biography.html |title=GrandesEstrellas.com: El sitio de las celebridades (The Site Of Celebrities) \u2013 Kike Santander \u2013 Biography |language=Spanish |author=Lena Hansen |accessdate=December 24, 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110317033531/http://www.grandesestrellas.com/k/kike-santander-biography.html |archivedate=March 17, 2011 }}</ref>\n\nAs a student, Santander tried his hand at a number of business ventures, such as starting a fish and seafood processing and distributing business,<ref name=\"KSMPM\"/> making toothpaste, plaster dolls and sausages. All of these failed and in the process his parents lost their house and savings.<ref name=\"JYL\" />\n\n== Musical career ==\n\n=== Beginning (1987\u20131993)===\nHe moved to [[Bogot\u00e1]] in 1987 where he worked as a jazz bassist<ref name=\"colarte\"/> and wrote his first song, \"El jard\u00edn de mis amores\" (The garden of my loves), at age 33, that was dedicated to his parents.<ref name=\"abc\"/> He met producer [[Bernardo Ossa]], who introduced him to the \"big leagues\" of advertising agencies, where he devoted his time and effort to write and produce commercial jingles, learning to make melodies that could be remembered. This work earned him the credibility of the advertising agencies in which he became the leading figure in this genre. Santander wrote and produced over 1500 jingles<ref name=\"colarte\">[http://www.colarte.com/colarte/conspintores.asp?idartista=12984 Kike Santander. Compositores] (translation: ColArte | Colombia| Kike Santander. Composers) | language=Spanish, by carlos Vanegas.</ref> in the 9 years in which he worked in commercial jingles.<ref name=\"abc\"/>\n\n=== Music career since 1993 ===\nIn 1993, he met Colombian musician [[Est\u00e9fano]], who offered him collaborate with him on an album for [[Jos\u00e9 Luis Rodr\u00edguez (singer)|Jos\u00e9 Luis Rodr\u00edguez \u00abEl Puma\u00bb]], composing his hit \"Diosito Santo\" (Dear God Holy).<ref name=\"abc\"/> Santander began his career as a composer and producer, working also for various Colombian artists such as Marcelo Cezan, for whom he wrote and produced the hits: \" Una en un mill\u00f3n\" (She is one in a million) and \"Hierba Mojada\" (Wet Grass) as well as for several local rock and pop bands. It was precisely in that year when Santander received his first award - the BMI award for the song \"Boca Dulce Boca\" (mouth, sweet mouth) a song he composed along with Stefano and Jos\u00e9 Luis Rodr\u00edguez, \"El Puma\". It was then, and due to his already recognized talent, that Santander joined forces with [[Emilio Estefan]].<ref name=\"GRESKI\"/> This experience officially marked the beginning of his career as a composer and music producer on January 7, 1994.\n\nIn 1995 Santander received a call from Emilio Estefan, who proposed that he write some songs for a Christmas album that [[Gloria Estefan]] would record. He agreed, and ended up writing all the songs for the production. The album (''[[Abriendo Puertas (Gloria Estefan album)|Abriendo Puertas]]'') became one of the most successful albums of Gloria Estefan. This was the start of an intense and extremely successful international career as a songwriter, producer and businessman in [[Miami]], Fl.<ref name=\"sucarrera\">{{cite news | url=http://www.elespectador.com/impreso/arteygente/gente/articuloimpreso-kike-santander-escribe-su-historia | publisher=El Espectador.com | title=Kike Santander escribe su historia (The Espectador.com: Kike Santander write their own history) | language=Spanish | author=Lina Mar\u00eda G\u00f3mez Gonz\u00e1lez}}\n</ref> In 1997 Santander created Santander Music Group, a company that is principally engaged in musical production. \n \nAfter Gloria Estefan's album ''[[Abriendo Puertas (Gloria Estefan album)|Abriendo Puertas]]'' (in which he composed all the songs<ref name=\"abc\"/>) he received the Latin Grammy for Best Tropical Album in 1997. During this year, he composed and produced six songs for the album \"Me Estoy Enamorando\" (I'm In Love) for [[Alejandro Fern\u00e1ndez]], who was nominated for a Grammy and sold more than three million copies worldwide, making the transition from Ranchero to the Pop music market. Santander also obtained his second Grammy Award for his song \"Mi Verdad\" (My Truth), performed by Alejandro Fern\u00e1ndez, winner for \"Best Regional Song\" and, in 1999, he also won a second consecutive award BMI \"Songwriter of the Year\" for \"Best Latin Song\" with \"[[Si T\u00fa Supieras]]\" (If You Knew). The following year (2000) he garnered the award \"Songwriter of the Year\" and four honorable mentions.<ref name=\"GRESKI\"/> In 2000, he was also honored with another [[Latin Grammy Awards]], this time in the \"Best Tropical Song\" for \"Swear\" performed by Giselle. In 2002, Santander received the [[Latin Grammy Award]] for [[Latin Grammy Award for Producer of the Year|Producer of the Year]] for his work on the tracks \"Perdidos En La Noche\", \"Por Ti Yo Ir\u00e9\", \"Que No Me Pierda\", \"Quisiera\", \"Si Tu Te Vas\" and \"Soy De La Gente\" by [[Diego Torres (singer)|Diego Torres]], and the albums ''[[Azul (Cristian Castro album)|Azul]]'' by [[Cristian Castro]] and ''Una Vez Mas'' by [[Jaime Camil]].\n\nDuring the same year, Santander also produced for artists such as [[Chayanne]], [[Amaury Guti\u00e9rrez]], [[Illegal (group)|Illegal]], [[Jaime Camil]] and [[Cristian Castro]], whose single \"Azul\" reached the top of the charts in USA and Latin America, and remained at number one in ''[[Billboard (Magazine)|Billboard]]''{{'}}s [[Hot Latin Songs]] for 11 consecutive weeks.<ref name=\"GRESKI\"/>\n\nSantander's career continued to rise by producing and writing hit after hit. In 2002 he produced \"[[Coraz\u00f3n Latino]]\", the first album of Spanish singer [[David Bisbal]], one of the most successful Latino singers. During this year, Santander also wrote the hit \"Por mas que intento\" (As much as I try) played by [[Gilberto Santa Rosa]], a song nominated for the Latin Grammy Awards for \"Best Tropical Song\". The song \"T\u00fa no Podr\u00e1s\" (You won't be able to) for [[Olga Ta\u00f1\u00f3n]], also successful on Billboard Magazine.<ref name=\"GRESKI\"/> In 2003, Santander produced the new album \"Prohibido Olvidar\" (No Forgetting) for [[Ricardo Montaner]], \"Natural\" for Noelia, \"As de Corazones\" (Ace of Hearts) for the Spanish [[Ra\u00fal Fuentes Cuenca|Ra\u00fal]] and \"[[Caramelito]]\" for [[Roc\u00edo D\u00farcal]]. For the production of Luis Miguel # 33 wrote the songs \"Devu\u00e9lveme el amor\" (Give me love) and \"Y sigo\" (And I keep). In 2004, he also produced the second album from David Bisbal, \"[[Buler\u00eda]]\".<ref>[http://www.latin-artists.com/biography.php?id=7&lang=_sp Latin-Artists.com - Artistas-Latinos.com - Kike Santander]</ref>\n\nIn 2007, he was named the Best Songwriter of The Year by Billboard magazine.<ref name=\"Kike Santander se reinventa\">[http://www.diariolibre.com/noticias_det.php?id=258901 Kike Santander trata de reinventarse. LA - DiarioLibre.com] (Kike Santander tries to reinvent himself in LA - DiarioLibre.com) (In Spanish).</ref>\n\nIn August 2010, he launched his label \"Santander Records\", primarily oriented towards regional Mexican music, and whose philosophy is to launch and develop different artists and position them.\n\nOn Thursday, March 10, 2011, Santander received in [[Las Vegas Valley|Las Vegas]] the President Award, the highest distinction of delivering the Latin BMI.<ref name=\"homenage\"/>\n\n== Other projects==\nAfter being one of the founding members and serving as Chairman of the Board of the Latin Grammy Academy for four consecutive years, Santander is currently their Chairman Emeritus. In 2002 he was named Chairman of the [[Latin Academy of Recording Arts & Sciences]], Inc.,<ref>[http://www.terra.com/entretenimiento/tv/noticias/kike_santander_explica_todo_lo_bueno_y_lo_malo_de_su_carrera/oci260473. Kike Santander explica todo lo bueno y lo malo de su carrera] (in Spanish: Kike Santander explains everything good and bad of his career) (In Spanish).</ref> and he is very involved with the talent show ''[[Operaci\u00f3n Triunfo (Spain)|Operaci\u00f3n Triunfo]]'' (a program of which he became director in 2005 and 2006).<ref>[https://archive.is/20130205154113/http://www.vertele.com/noticias/9951/kike-santander-sustituye-nina-frente-academia. Kike Santander sustituye a Nina al frente de la Academia de \"OT\"] (Kike Santander replaces Nina at the head of the Academy of \"OT\") (in Spanish)</ref>\n\nIn 2005 Santander moved to [[Barcelona]], Spain where he created BATUKA,<ref>[http://www.batuka.com BATUKA]</ref> a group fitness workout method with original music he composed. BATUKA was launched on the Spanish market in July 2005 and became an instant phenomenon selling more than 1.5 million DVDs in the first 16 months in Spain only. BATUKA created a new trend in the way to do group fitness and started expanding to other European countries such as Italy, Germany and France. BATUKA is going through an aggressive expansion phase with the creation of six new fitness programs for the health club market as well as its own nutrition method created and developed by Miriam Nelson, one of the most respected authorities in nutrition in the US, as well as its own \" Batuka Philosophy\" created by Santander, which is a way to educate people about how to achieve a more balanced way of life and a more harmonious inner state. BATUKA was officially launched in North America in 2011 and the rest of Europe in 2012.<ref>[http://www.elmundo.com/sitio/noticia_detalle.php?idcuerpo=2&dscuerpo=La%20Metro&idseccion=27&dsseccion=Entretenimiento&idnoticia=157963&imagen=&vl=1&r=primera_pagina.php&idedicion=1846.El Mundo.com] (The World.com) (In Spanish)</ref>\n\nIn 2007, Santander also partnered with the renowned musician, composer and producer [[Mark Portmann]] to start a company to create music for film and television.<ref name=\"Kike Santander se reinventa\"/> In 2008 he published an autobiography, ''Por amor a la m\u00fasica'' (For the love of music). The book comes with a CD with the \"Cancionero de su vida\" (in Spanish: song of his life) in which the composer sings the themes that more thrill him. The repertoire ranges from a lullaby his mother sang to him, to hits like \"Quiero perderme en tu cuerpo\" (I wanna get lost in your body) (David Bisbal). Also in 2008, he composed the music for the stage version of ''[[Like Water for Chocolate (novel)|Como agua para chocolate]]'' (Like Water for Chocolate), based on the novel by Mexican writer Laura Esquivel, which premiered on Broadway in 2009.<ref name=\"JYL\">{{cite news|date=February 27, 2008|url=http://www.peopleenespanol.com/pespanol/articles/0,22490,1717827,00.html|title=Las lecciones de vida de Kike Santander (The life lessons of Kike Santander)|language=Spanish|author=Lena Hansen|accessdate=December 14, 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101207065941/http://www.peopleenespanol.com/pespanol/articles/0,22490,1717827,00.html|archive-date=December 7, 2010|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nSince late 2013, Kike Santander has been the advisor of the 2\u00ba season of contest \"[[La Voz Colombia]]\".<ref>[http://www.jairomartinez.com/kike-santander-la-gran-sensacion-de-la-voz-colombia/ Jairo Mart\u00ednez: Kike Santander la gran sensaci\u00f3n de \u201cla Voz Colombia\u201d] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131110031917/http://www.jairomartinez.com/kike-santander-la-gran-sensacion-de-la-voz-colombia/ |date=November 10, 2013 }} (in Spanish:Kike Santander the great feeling of \"the Voice Colombia). Posted by admin on septiembre 19, 2013. Retrieved November 10, 2013, to 2:40pm.</ref>\n\nIn February 2014, Santander launched the QiClub program,<ref>[http://musica.univision.com/noticias/article/2014-03-26/kike-santander-unio-las-tres-mejores-etapas-de-su-vida Kike Santander uni\u00f3 sus dos pasiones: la m\u00fasica y la medicina] (in Spanish: Kike Santander joined his two passions: music and medicine). Posted by March 26, 2014. Retrieved in February 15, 2015, to 17:09 pm.</ref> an online service online and via monthly subscription, with which people do fitness exercises from their phone or from their tablet. The program has videos of fitness trainers, fitness, a Colombian national, who teach these things. The videos were recorded in Los Angeles to present on television and offer this service through the platforms. Fitness has three programs, one dance; another hike and one more musical strengthening. All these initiatives have original music composed by Santander.<ref>[http://www.elespectador.com/entretenimiento/agenda/musica/fitness-el-nuevo-proyecto-de-kike-santander-articulo-430259 Fitness, el nuevo proyecto de Kike Santander] (in Spanish: Fitness, the new draft Kike Santander). Posted in M\u00fasica June 27, 2013, to 11:07 am. Retrieved in February 15, 2015, to 17:04 pm..</ref>\n\n== Musical influence ==\nSantander was heavily influenced by the Colombian and international folklore that his parents listened to (especially the Mexican music that his father frequently listed to) during his childhood. Also, during his teens, he frequently listened to tropical music, pop and rock of the '70s, both jazz and classical music. All these styles would be influential in his understanding of music and would influence the way he wrote and composed his songs.<ref name=\"abc\"/>\n\n== Personal life ==\nIn 2001 Santander sued Emilio Estefan for breach of contract, lack of benefit payments and for the title of Producer, where supposedly Estefan was not physically present, thus ending a successful business relationship which began in 1995.<ref name=\"sucarrera\"/>\n\nSantander has married twice. With his first wife, Gloria Alvarez, he had a son named Sebastian Santander. Now he is married to [[Paraguay]]an Adriana L\u00f3pez.<ref name=\"patenimiento\">[http://www.elpais.com.co/elpais/entretenimiento/noticias/vida-kike-santander-contada-por-sus-seres-cercanos La vida de Kike Santander contada por sus seres m\u00e1s cercanos] (in Spanish: Kike Santander's life told by their loved ones). Posted by Isabel Pelaez, Reporter of newspapers ''[[El Pa\u00eds]]''. Sunday, September 29, 2013. Retrieved November 10, 2013, to 2:16pm.</ref><ref name=\"JYL\" /> The couple have two children: Andrea, Adriana's daughter from a previous relationship; and Alejandro, born to the couple in 2008. In 2004 Santander became a naturalized US citizen,<ref name=\"JYL\" /> and the family settled in [[Huntington Park, California]] in October 2010.\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n\n===''Billboard'' Latin Music Awards===\nSantander has received the following [[Billboard Latin Music Awards|''Billboard'' Latin Music Awards]] and nominations.<ref name=\"LMBA\">''Billboard'' Latin Music Awards:\n\n*'''1999 Awards''': {{cite journal\n|title=10th Annual Billboard Latin Music Conference\n|last=Lannert\n|first=John\n|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=eigEAAAAMBAJ&lpg=PA7&pg=RA1-PA42#v=onepage&q&f=false\n|work=Billboard\n|publisher=Prometheus Global Media\n|volume=111\n|issue=17\n|page=42\n|date=April 24, 1999\n|accessdate=June 29, 2015\n}}\n\n*'''2000 Awards''': {{cite journal\n|title=Catch Some Rising Stars\n|last=Lannert\n|first=John\n|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=EA8EAAAAMBAJ&lpg=PP1&pg=RA1-PA20#v=onepage&q&f=false\n|work=Billboard\n|publisher=Prometheus Global Media\n|volume=112\n|issue=18\n|page=LM-18\n|date=April 29, 2000\n|accessdate=June 29, 2015\n}}\n\n*'''2001 Awards''': {{cite journal\n|title=Billboard Awards Recognizes The Best in Latin Music\n|last=Coco\n|first=Leila\n|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=oxMEAAAAMBAJ&lpg=PA1&pg=PA56#v=onepage&q&f=false\n|work=Billboard\n|publisher=Prometheus Global Media\n|volume=113\n|issue=17\n|page=LM-6\n|date=November 30, 2004\n|accessdate=June 29, 2015\n}}\n\n*'''2004 Awards''': {{cite journal\n|title=2004 Billboard Music Awards\n|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/65464/2004-billboard-music-awards-finalists\n|work=Billboard\n|publisher=Prometheus Global Media\n|date=May 5, 2001\n|accessdate=June 29, 2015\n}}\n\n</ref>\n\n{{awards table}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" scope=\"row\"| 1999\n|rowspan=\"7\" scope=\"row\"| Himself\n|scope=\"row\"|Songwriter of the Year\n| {{won}}\n|-\n|scope=\"row\"| Producer of the Year\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" scope=\"row\"| 2000\n|scope=\"row\"|Songwriter of the Year\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Producer of the Year\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" scope=\"row\"| 2001\n|scope=\"row\"|Songwriter of the Year\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" scope=\"row\"| Producer of the Year\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n|[[2004 Latin Billboard Music Awards|2004]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n{{end}}\n\n===BMI Latin awards===\nSantander has won the following [[Broadcast Music, Inc.|BMI]] awards.<ref name=\"BMI\">BMI Awards:\n\n*'''1997 Awards''': {{cite journal\n|title=Los Premios Latino de BMI\n|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=AQoEAAAAMBAJ&lpg=PA1&pg=PA85#v=onepage&q&f=false\n|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]\n|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]\n|page=85\n|date=September 13, 1997\n|accessdate=June 29, 2015\n}}\n\n*'''1999 Awards''': {{cite journal\n|title=Los Premios Latinos de BMI Latin 1999\n|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=CQ0EAAAAMBAJ&lpg=PA1&pg=RA1-PA33#v=onepage&q&f=false\n|work=Billboard\n|publisher=Prometheus Global Media\n|volume=111\n|issue=26\n|page=33\n|date=June 26, 1999\n|accessdate=June 29, 2015\n}}\n\n*'''2000 Awards''': {{cite web\n|title=BMI Honors Top Latin Writers and Publishers\n|url=http://www.bmi.com/news/entry/20000502_bmi_honors_top_latin_writers_and_publishers\n|publisher=Broadcast Music, Inc.\n|date=May 1, 2000\n|accessdate=June 29, 2015\n}}\n\n*'''2001 Awards''': {{cite journal\n|title=Three Writers Tie For BMI Latin Award\n|last=Pesselnick\n|first=Jill\n|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=BBQEAAAAMBAJ&lpg=PA1&pg=PA9#v=onepage&q&f=false\n|work=Billboard\n|publisher=Prometheus Global Media\n|volume=113\n|issue=18\n|page=9\n|date=May 5, 2001\n|accessdate=June 29, 2015\n}}\n\n*'''2002 Awards''': {{cite web\n|title=2002 BMI Latin Awards: Song List\n|url=http://www.bmi.com/news/entry/2002_bmi_latin_awards_song_list\n|publisher=Broadcast Music, Inc.\n|date=May 7, 2002\n|accessdate=June 29, 2015\n}}\n\n*'''2004 Awards''': {{cite web\n|title=2004 BMI Latin Awards: Song List\n|url=http://www.bmi.com/news/entry/2004_bmi_latin_awards_song_list\n|publisher=Broadcast Music, Inc.\n|date=March 15, 2004\n|accessdate=June 29, 2015\n}}\n\n*'''2005 Awards''': {{cite web\n|title=BMI Songwriters and Publishers Win Big at 12th Annual Latin Awards in Las Vegas\n|url=http://www.bmi.com/news/entry/20050422_bmi_songwriters_and_publishers_win_big_at_12th_annual_latin_a\n|publisher=Broadcast Music, Inc.\n|date=April 21, 2005\n|accessdate=June 29, 2015\n}}\n\n*'''2006 Awards''': {{cite web\n|title=Juan Luis Guerra, Juanes Top 13th Annual BMI Latin Awards\n|url=http://www.bmi.com/news/entry/20060407_juan_luis_guerra_juanes_top_13th_annual_bmi_latin_awards\n|publisher=Broadcast Music, Inc.\n|date=April 6, 2006\n|accessdate=June 29, 2015\n}}\n\n*'''2008 Awards''': {{cite web\n|title=Juan Luis Guerra, Juanes Top 13th Annual BMI Latin Awards\n|url=http://www.bmi.com/news/entry/gustavo_santaolalla_named_icon_at_15th_annual_bmi_latin_music_awards\n|publisher=Broadcast Music, Inc.\n|date=June 13, 2008\n|accessdate=June 29, 2015\n}}\n\n*'''2011 Awards''': {{cite web\n|title=Kike Santander to Receive BMI President's Award at 18th Annual BMI Latin Music Awards\n|url=http://www.bmi.com/news/entry/kike_santander_to_receive_bmi_presidents_award_at_18th_annual_bmi_lati\n|publisher=Broadcast Music, Inc.\n|date=February 3, 2011\n|accessdate=June 29, 2015\n}}\n\n</ref>\n\n{{awards table}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" scope=\"row\"| 1997\n|scope=\"row\"| \"[[Abriendo Puertas (song)|Abriendo Puertas]]\"\n|rowspan=\"2\" scope=\"row\"| Award-winning songs\n| {{won}}\n|-\n|scope=\"row\"| \"[[Piel Morena]]\"\n| {{won}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"7\" scope=\"row\"| 1999\n|scope=\"row\"| Himself\n|Songwriter of the Year\n| {{won}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" |\"[[Si T\u00fa Supieras]]\"\n|Song of the Year\n| {{won}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"5\"|Award-winning songs\n| {{won}}\n|-\n|\"[[Heaven's What I Feel|Corazon Prohibido]]\"\n| {{won}}\n|-\n|\"[[En El Jardin]]\"\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| \"[[No S\u00e9 Olvidar]]\"\n| {{won}}\n|-\n|\"Yo Naci Para Amarte\"\n| {{won}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\" scope=\"row\"| 2000\n|scope=\"row\"| Himself\n|Songwriter of the Year\n| {{won}}\n|-\n|\"Decir Adios\"\n|rowspan=\"3\"|Award-winning songs\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| \"Te Vas\"\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| \"Tu Amor\"\n| {{won}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"5\" scope=\"row\"| 2001\n|scope=\"row\"| Himself\n|Songwriter of the Year\n| {{won}}\n|-\n|\"Alguna Vez\"\n|rowspan=\"14\" |Award-winning songs\n| {{won}}\n|-\n|\"[[Da la Vuelta]]\"\n| {{won}}\n|-\n|\"Mi Vida Sin Tu Amor\"\n| {{won}}\n|-\n|\"Volver a Amar\"\n| {{won}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\" scope=\"row\"| 2002\n|\"[[Azul (song)|Azul]]\"\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| \"Jurame\"\n| {{won}}\n|-\n|\"Si Te Vas\"\n| {{won}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\" scope=\"row\"| 2004\n|\"Con Ella\"\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| \"Entre el Delirio y la Locura\"\n| {{won}}\n|-\n|\"Por Mas Que Intento\"\n| {{won}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" scope=\"row\"| 2005\n|\"No Podras\"\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| \"Quiero Perderme en Tu Cuerpo\"\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| 2006\n|\"[[Buleria (David Bisbal song)|Buleria]]\"\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| 2008\n|\"[[\u00bfQui\u00e9n Me Iba a Decir?]]\"\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| 2011\n|Himself\n|BMI's President Award\n| {{won}}\n|-\n{{end}}\n\n===Latin Grammy Awards===\nSantander has received the following [[Latin Grammy Award]]s and nominations.<ref name=\"LGA\">Latin Grammy Awards:\n\n*'''2000 Awards''': {{cite web\n|title=Santana, Luis Miguel, Man\u00e1 Lead Latin Grammy Winners\n|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1431652/santana-luis-miguel-man-lead-latin-grammy-winners/\n|publisher=[[MTV]]\n|date=September 14, 2000\n|accessdate=June 29, 2015\n}}\n\n*'''2001 Awards''': {{cite web\n|title=Latin Recording Academy Announces 2nd Annual Latin Grammy Award Winners\n|url=http://laprensa-sandiego.org/archieve/november02/4grammy.htm\n|work=La Prensa San Diego\n|date=November 2, 2001\n|accessdate=June 30, 2015\n}}\n*'''2002 Awards''': {{cite web\n|title=List of winners at the 3rd annual Latin Grammy awards\n|url=http://lasvegassun.com/news/2002/sep/19/list-of-winners-at-the-3rd-annual-latin-grammy-awa/\n|publisher=[[Las Vegas Sun]]\n|date=September 19, 2002\n|accessdate=June 29, 2015\n}}\n\n</ref>\n\n{{awards table}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" scope=\"row\"| [[Latin Grammy Awards of 2000|2000]]\n|scope=\"row\"| \"Mi Verdad\"\n|[[Latin Grammy Award for Best Regional Song|Best Regional Song]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n|\"[[Da la Vuelta]]\"\n|rowspan=\"2\" scope=\"row\"|[[Latin Grammy Award for Best Tropical Song|Best Tropical Song]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Latin Grammy Awards of 2001|2001]]\n|scope=\"row\"| \"Jurame\"\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Latin Grammy Awards of 2002|2002]]\n|scope=\"row\"| Himself\n|[[Latin Grammy Award for Producer of the Year|Producer of the Year]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n{{end}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|33em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.cromos.com.co/actualidad/articulo-149218-%C2%ABbeyonce-la-cantante-mas-sexi%C2%BB-kike-santander Kike Santander trivia]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20080201002121/http://www.emimusicpub.com/worldwide/artist_profile/kike-santander_profile.html]\n* [https://www.flickr.com/photos/proteusbcn/3256686350/in/set-72157613401255026/ Free pic]\n* [http://www.kikemusic.com/ Kike Santander fan site] - news and discography of Kike Santander (in Spanish)\n* [http://www.eluniversal.com.co/suplementos/facetas/kike-santander-el-cirujano-de-la-musica-137189 Kike Santander: El cirujano de la m\u00fasica] (In Spanish. Kike Santander: The surgeon of music)\n* [http://www.discaffinity.com/es/productor/kike-santander Beta Disc Affinity: Discos producidos por Kike Santander] (in Spanish: albums produced by Kike Santander)\n{{Operaci\u00f3n Triunfo}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Santander, Kike}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Colombian musicians]]\n[[Category:University of Valle alumni]]\n[[Category:Colombian record producers]]\n[[Category:Colombian emigrants to the United States]]\n[[Category:Record producers from California]]\n[[Category:Latin Grammy Award for Producer of the Year]]\n[[Category:People from Cali]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Los Angeles]]\n[[Category:Jingle composers]]\n[[Category:People with acquired American citizenship]]\n[[Category:Latin music record producers]]\n[[Category:American people of Colombian descent]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n", "text_old": "{{Spanish name|Santander|Lora}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2019}}\n{{Infobox musical artist  <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject Musicians -->\n| name = Kike Santander\n| image = Kike Santander en Eurovisi\u00f3n 2004.jpg\n| caption = \n| image_size = \n| background          =  non_performing_personnel\n| birth_name          = Flavio Enrique Santander Lora\n| alias               = \n| birth_date=\n| birth_place=[[Santiago de Cali]], [[Colombia]]\n| death_date=\n| death_place=\n| occupation          = Composer and producer\n| years_active        = 1987\u2013present\n| Label              \n| Associated_a\n\n| label = Santander Records\n| website                 = [http://kikesantander.com/ KikeSantander.com] \u2013 official site in Spanish and English\n}}\n\n'''Flavio Enrique \"Kike\" Santander Lora''' is a [[Colombian Americans|Colombian-American]] composer, record producer, arranger and entrepreneur.<ref name=\"homenage\"/> He is considered to be one of the principal Latino composers of the day, having worked with artists such as [[David Bisbal]], [[Cristian Castro]], [[Thal\u00eda]], [[Chayanne]], [[Diego Torres (singer)|Diego Torres]], [[Davi Wornel]], [[Alejandro Fern\u00e1ndez]], [[Olga Ta\u00f1\u00f3n]], [[Bacilos]], [[Jos\u00e9 Luis Rodr\u00edguez (singer)|Jos\u00e9 Luis Rodr\u00edguez \u00abEl Puma\u00bb]] and [[Gloria Estefan]] among others.<ref name=\"KSMPM\">{{cite news|date=February 27, 2008 |url=http://www.revistadiners.com.co/noticia.php3?nt=23098 |title=Diners Journal:: The Magazine of the Month. Mi primer mill\u00f3n (Diners Journal: Journal of Mes. The first million) |language=Spanish |author=Constanza Morales Arias |accessdate=December 20, 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20040107043258/http://www.revistadiners.com.co/noticia.php3?nt=23098 |archivedate= January 7, 2004 }}</ref> Santander has composed more than 710 songs and has sold over 25 million albums worldwide.<ref name=\"homenage\">[http://50.22.195.205/noticia-670817.html?intId=670817 La Vanguardia: Kike Santander recibir\u00e1 homenaje en Las Vegas] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131110035848/http://50.22.195.205/noticia-670817.html?intId=670817 |date=November 10, 2013 }}  (in Spanish: Kike Santander will receive homage in Las Vegas). Posted in Thursday, March 10, 2011. Retrieved November 10, 2013, to 2:51pm.</ref> His work as songwriter and producer includes themes such as ''[[Let's Get Loud (Jennifer Lopez song)|Let's Get Loud]]'' by [[Jennifer Lopez]], ''[[Abriendo puertas (song)|Abriendo puertas]]'' by Gloria Estefan, ''[[Me Estoy Enamorando (album)|Me Estoy Enamorando]]'' by Alejandro Fern\u00e1ndez, ''[[Mi Vida Sin Tu Amor]]'' by Cristian Castro, and ''[[Premonici\u00f3n]]'' by David Bisbal, as well as many songs recorded by artists such as Thal\u00eda, [[Natalia Oreiro]], [[Gisselle]], [[Edith M\u00e1rquez]], [[Luis Miguel]], [[Soledad Pastorutti]] and the Spanish song for [[Eurovision Song Contest 2004]], amongst others.\n\nMore than 25 of his songs have been in the coveted Top Ten, as reflected in the Latin ''Billboard'' charts since 1999. More than 15 of his songs are featured within the top 100 played songs by the BMI Association of Authors and Composers. His songs and productions have surpassed 25 million albums worldwide <ref name=\"KSMPM\"/> and he has won prizes and awards that are given in the music industry on multiple occasions: [[Grammy Awards]], [[Billboard Music Award|Billboard]], [[Lo Nuestro Awards]], [[Premios TVyNovelas]], El Heraldo, and [[Broadcast Music Incorporated|BMI]] in which he has received the most awards in its Latin division, and many more.<ref name=\"GRESKI\"/> His brother is the composer [[Gustavo Santander]].\n\n== Early years ==\nKike Santander was born in [[Santiago de Cali]], [[Colombia]], and he was raised in La Flora, a typical upper-middle-class neighborhood of Cali. His father was the dentist, poet and guitarist Flavio Santander and his mother's name is Judith. His brother is the composer [[Gustavo Santander]]. In Cali he spent his first years learning different rhythms and musical skills while studying at Colegio Berchmans from which he graduated in 1977. He began his musical studies at an early age, playing the accordion (his first instrument, which he played since age 8) and experimenting with instruments like acoustic guitar (to age 12), electric guitar (to age 13), lira, the electric bass (to age 16), piano and later devoted himself to the percussion (to age 18).<ref name=\"abc\">[http://www.abc.com.py/nota/kike-santander-me-siento-mitad-paraguayo/ Digital ABC: Kike Santander: \u201cMe siento mitad paraguayo\u201d] (In Spanish: Kike Santander: \"I feel that am half Paraguayan\"). Published January 6, 2012, to 19:00 pm. Retrieved March 15, 2011, to 23:21 pm.</ref> His earliest musical influences came from a wide mix of genres that include indigenous artists of his native country. His main influences were [[bolero]], [[rock and roll]], Anglo-American [[pop music|pop]], [[classical music]] and [[jazz]]. He studied music at the Cali Conservatory. In 1978, when he was 18, he began his medical studies at the [[University of Valle]] from which he graduated in Medicine and Surgery.<ref name=\"GRESKI\"/> He worked as a doctor for one year before deciding to dedicate himself completely to studying music and his musical career.<ref name=\"abc\"/><ref name=\"GRESKI\">{{cite news|date=February 27, 2008 |url=http://www.grandesestrellas.com/k/kike-santander-biography.html |title=GrandesEstrellas.com: El sitio de las celebridades (The Site Of Celebrities) \u2013 Kike Santander \u2013 Biography |language=Spanish |author=Lena Hansen |accessdate=December 24, 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110317033531/http://www.grandesestrellas.com/k/kike-santander-biography.html |archivedate=March 17, 2011 }}</ref>\n\nAs a student, Santander tried his hand at a number of business ventures, such as starting a fish and seafood processing and distributing business,<ref name=\"KSMPM\"/> making toothpaste, plaster dolls and sausages. All of these failed and in the process his parents lost their house and savings.<ref name=\"JYL\" />\n\n== Musical career ==\n\n=== Beginning (1987\u20131993)===\nHe moved to [[Bogot\u00e1]] in 1987 where he worked as a jazz bassist<ref name=\"colarte\"/> and wrote his first song, \"El jard\u00edn de mis amores\" (The garden of my loves), at age 33, that was dedicated to his parents.<ref name=\"abc\"/> He met producer [[Bernardo Ossa]], who introduced him to the \"big leagues\" of advertising agencies, where he devoted his time and effort to write and produce commercial jingles, learning to make melodies that could be remembered. This work earned him the credibility of the advertising agencies in which he became the leading figure in this genre. Santander wrote and produced over 1500 jingles<ref name=\"colarte\">[http://www.colarte.com/colarte/conspintores.asp?idartista=12984 Kike Santander. Compositores] (translation: ColArte | Colombia| Kike Santander. Composers) | language=Spanish, by carlos Vanegas.</ref> in the 9 years in which he worked in commercial jingles.<ref name=\"abc\"/>\n\n=== Music career since 1993 ===\nIn 1993, he met Colombian musician [[Est\u00e9fano]], who offered him collaborate with him on an album for [[Jos\u00e9 Luis Rodr\u00edguez (singer)|Jos\u00e9 Luis Rodr\u00edguez \u00abEl Puma\u00bb]], composing his hit \"Diosito Santo\" (Dear God Holy).<ref name=\"abc\"/> Santander began his career as a composer and producer, working also for various Colombian artists such as Marcelo Cezan, for whom he wrote and produced the hits: \" Una en un mill\u00f3n\" (She is one in a million) and \"Hierba Mojada\" (Wet Grass) as well as for several local rock and pop bands. It was precisely in that year when Santander received his first award - the BMI award for the song \"Boca Dulce Boca\" (mouth, sweet mouth) a song he composed along with Stefano and Jos\u00e9 Luis Rodr\u00edguez, \"El Puma\". It was then, and due to his already recognized talent, that Santander joined forces with [[Emilio Estefan]].<ref name=\"GRESKI\"/> This experience officially marked the beginning of his career as a composer and music producer on January 7, 1994.\n\nIn 1995 Santander received a call from Emilio Estefan, who proposed that he write some songs for a Christmas album that [[Gloria Estefan]] would record. He agreed, and ended up writing all the songs for the production. The album (''[[Abriendo Puertas (Gloria Estefan album)|Abriendo Puertas]]'') became one of the most successful albums of Gloria Estefan. This was the start of an intense and extremely successful international career as a songwriter, producer and businessman in [[Miami]], Fl.<ref name=\"sucarrera\">{{cite news | url=http://www.elespectador.com/impreso/arteygente/gente/articuloimpreso-kike-santander-escribe-su-historia | publisher=El Espectador.com | title=Kike Santander escribe su historia (The Espectador.com: Kike Santander write their own history) | language=Spanish | author=Lina Mar\u00eda G\u00f3mez Gonz\u00e1lez}}\n</ref> In 1997 Santander created Santander Music Group, a company that is principally engaged in musical production. \n \nAfter Gloria Estefan's album ''[[Abriendo Puertas (Gloria Estefan album)|Abriendo Puertas]]'' (in which he composed all the songs<ref name=\"abc\"/>) he received the Latin Grammy for Best Tropical Album in 1997. During this year, he composed and produced six songs for the album \"Me Estoy Enamorando\" (I'm In Love) for [[Alejandro Fern\u00e1ndez]], who was nominated for a Grammy and sold more than three million copies worldwide, making the transition from Ranchero to the Pop music market. Santander also obtained his second Grammy Award for his song \"Mi Verdad\" (My Truth), performed by Alejandro Fern\u00e1ndez, winner for \"Best Regional Song\" and, in 1999, he also won a second consecutive award BMI \"Songwriter of the Year\" for \"Best Latin Song\" with \"[[Si T\u00fa Supieras]]\" (If You Knew). The following year (2000) he garnered the award \"Songwriter of the Year\" and four honorable mentions.<ref name=\"GRESKI\"/> In 2000, he was also honored with another [[Latin Grammy Awards]], this time in the \"Best Tropical Song\" for \"Swear\" performed by Giselle. In 2002, Santander received the [[Latin Grammy Award]] for [[Latin Grammy Award for Producer of the Year|Producer of the Year]] for his work on the tracks \"Perdidos En La Noche\", \"Por Ti Yo Ir\u00e9\", \"Que No Me Pierda\", \"Quisiera\", \"Si Tu Te Vas\" and \"Soy De La Gente\" by [[Diego Torres (singer)|Diego Torres]], and the albums ''[[Azul (Cristian Castro album)|Azul]]'' by [[Cristian Castro]] and ''Una Vez Mas'' by [[Jaime Camil]].\n\nDuring the same year, Santander also produced for artists such as [[Chayanne]], [[Amaury Guti\u00e9rrez]], [[Illegal (group)|Illegal]], [[Jaime Camil]] and [[Cristian Castro]], whose single \"Azul\" reached the top of the charts in USA and Latin America, and remained at number one in ''[[Billboard (Magazine)|Billboard]]''{{'}}s [[Hot Latin Songs]] for 11 consecutive weeks.<ref name=\"GRESKI\"/>\n\nSantander's career continued to rise by producing and writing hit after hit. In 2002 he produced \"[[Coraz\u00f3n Latino]]\", the first album of Spanish singer [[David Bisbal]], one of the most successful Latino singers. During this year, Santander also wrote the hit \"Por mas que intento\" (As much as I try) played by [[Gilberto Santa Rosa]], a song nominated for the Latin Grammy Awards for \"Best Tropical Song\". The song \"T\u00fa no Podr\u00e1s\" (You won't be able to) for [[Olga Ta\u00f1\u00f3n]], also successful on Billboard Magazine.<ref name=\"GRESKI\"/> In 2003, Santander produced the new album \"Prohibido Olvidar\" (No Forgetting) for [[Ricardo Montaner]], \"Natural\" for Noelia, \"As de Corazones\" (Ace of Hearts) for the Spanish [[Ra\u00fal Fuentes Cuenca|Ra\u00fal]] and \"[[Caramelito]]\" for [[Roc\u00edo D\u00farcal]]. For the production of Luis Miguel # 33 wrote the songs \"Devu\u00e9lveme el amor\" (Give me love) and \"Y sigo\" (And I keep). In 2004, he also produced the second album from David Bisbal, \"[[Buler\u00eda]]\".<ref>[http://www.latin-artists.com/biography.php?id=7&lang=_sp Latin-Artists.com - Artistas-Latinos.com - Kike Santander]</ref>\n\nIn 2007, he was named the Best Songwriter of The Year by Billboard magazine.<ref name=\"Kike Santander se reinventa\">[http://www.diariolibre.com/noticias_det.php?id=258901 Kike Santander trata de reinventarse. LA - DiarioLibre.com] (Kike Santander tries to reinvent himself in LA - DiarioLibre.com) (In Spanish).</ref>\n\nIn August 2010, he launched his label \"Santander Records\", primarily oriented towards regional Mexican music, and whose philosophy is to launch and develop different artists and position them.\n\nOn Thursday, March 10, 2011, Santander received in [[Las Vegas Valley|Las Vegas]] the President Award, the highest distinction of delivering the Latin BMI.<ref name=\"homenage\"/>\n\n== Other projects==\nAfter being one of the founding members and serving as Chairman of the Board of the Latin Grammy Academy for four consecutive years, Santander is currently their Chairman Emeritus. In 2002 he was named Chairman of the [[Latin Academy of Recording Arts & Sciences]], Inc.,<ref>[http://www.terra.com/entretenimiento/tv/noticias/kike_santander_explica_todo_lo_bueno_y_lo_malo_de_su_carrera/oci260473. Kike Santander explica todo lo bueno y lo malo de su carrera] (in Spanish: Kike Santander explains everything good and bad of his career) (In Spanish).</ref> and he is very involved with the talent show ''[[Operaci\u00f3n Triunfo (Spain)|Operaci\u00f3n Triunfo]]'' (a program of which he became director in 2005 and 2006).<ref>[https://archive.is/20130205154113/http://www.vertele.com/noticias/9951/kike-santander-sustituye-nina-frente-academia. Kike Santander sustituye a Nina al frente de la Academia de \"OT\"] (Kike Santander replaces Nina at the head of the Academy of \"OT\") (in Spanish)</ref>\n\nIn 2005 Santander moved to [[Barcelona]], Spain where he created BATUKA,<ref>[http://www.batuka.com BATUKA]</ref> a group fitness workout method with original music he composed. BATUKA was launched on the Spanish market in July 2005 and became an instant phenomenon selling more than 1.5 million DVDs in the first 16 months in Spain only. BATUKA created a new trend in the way to do group fitness and started expanding to other European countries such as Italy, Germany and France. BATUKA is going through an aggressive expansion phase with the creation of six new fitness programs for the health club market as well as its own nutrition method created and developed by Miriam Nelson, one of the most respected authorities in nutrition in the US, as well as its own \" Batuka Philosophy\" created by Santander, which is a way to educate people about how to achieve a more balanced way of life and a more harmonious inner state. BATUKA was officially launched in North America in 2011 and the rest of Europe in 2012.<ref>[http://www.elmundo.com/sitio/noticia_detalle.php?idcuerpo=2&dscuerpo=La%20Metro&idseccion=27&dsseccion=Entretenimiento&idnoticia=157963&imagen=&vl=1&r=primera_pagina.php&idedicion=1846.El Mundo.com] (The World.com) (In Spanish)</ref>\n\nIn 2007, Santander also partnered with the renowned musician, composer and producer [[Mark Portmann]] to start a company to create music for film and television.<ref name=\"Kike Santander se reinventa\"/> In 2008 he published an autobiography, ''Por amor a la m\u00fasica'' (For the love of music). The book comes with a CD with the \"Cancionero de su vida\" (in Spanish: song of his life) in which the composer sings the themes that more thrill him. The repertoire ranges from a lullaby his mother sang to him, to hits like \"Quiero perderme en tu cuerpo\" (I wanna get lost in your body) (David Bisbal). Also in 2008, he composed the music for the stage version of ''[[Como agua para chocolate]]'' (Like Water for Chocolate), based on the novel by Mexican writer Laura Esquivel, which premiered on Broadway in 2009.<ref name=\"JYL\">{{cite news|date=February 27, 2008|url=http://www.peopleenespanol.com/pespanol/articles/0,22490,1717827,00.html|title=Las lecciones de vida de Kike Santander (The life lessons of Kike Santander)|language=Spanish|author=Lena Hansen|accessdate=December 14, 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101207065941/http://www.peopleenespanol.com/pespanol/articles/0,22490,1717827,00.html|archive-date=December 7, 2010|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nSince late 2013, Kike Santander has been the advisor of the 2\u00ba season of contest \"[[La Voz Colombia]]\".<ref>[http://www.jairomartinez.com/kike-santander-la-gran-sensacion-de-la-voz-colombia/ Jairo Mart\u00ednez: Kike Santander la gran sensaci\u00f3n de \u201cla Voz Colombia\u201d] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131110031917/http://www.jairomartinez.com/kike-santander-la-gran-sensacion-de-la-voz-colombia/ |date=November 10, 2013 }} (in Spanish:Kike Santander the great feeling of \"the Voice Colombia). Posted by admin on septiembre 19, 2013. Retrieved November 10, 2013, to 2:40pm.</ref>\n\nIn February 2014, Santander launched the QiClub program,<ref>[http://musica.univision.com/noticias/article/2014-03-26/kike-santander-unio-las-tres-mejores-etapas-de-su-vida Kike Santander uni\u00f3 sus dos pasiones: la m\u00fasica y la medicina] (in Spanish: Kike Santander joined his two passions: music and medicine). Posted by March 26, 2014. Retrieved in February 15, 2015, to 17:09 pm.</ref> an online service online and via monthly subscription, with which people do fitness exercises from their phone or from their tablet. The program has videos of fitness trainers, fitness, a Colombian national, who teach these things. The videos were recorded in Los Angeles to present on television and offer this service through the platforms. Fitness has three programs, one dance; another hike and one more musical strengthening. All these initiatives have original music composed by Santander.<ref>[http://www.elespectador.com/entretenimiento/agenda/musica/fitness-el-nuevo-proyecto-de-kike-santander-articulo-430259 Fitness, el nuevo proyecto de Kike Santander] (in Spanish: Fitness, the new draft Kike Santander). Posted in M\u00fasica June 27, 2013, to 11:07 am. Retrieved in February 15, 2015, to 17:04 pm..</ref>\n\n== Musical influence ==\nSantander was heavily influenced by the Colombian and international folklore that his parents listened to (especially the Mexican music that his father frequently listed to) during his childhood. Also, during his teens, he frequently listened to tropical music, pop and rock of the '70s, both jazz and classical music. All these styles would be influential in his understanding of music and would influence the way he wrote and composed his songs.<ref name=\"abc\"/>\n\n== Personal life ==\nIn 2001 Santander sued Emilio Estefan for breach of contract, lack of benefit payments and for the title of Producer, where supposedly Estefan was not physically present, thus ending a successful business relationship which began in 1995.<ref name=\"sucarrera\"/>\n\nSantander has married twice. With his first wife, Gloria Alvarez, he had a son named Sebastian Santander. Now he is married to [[Paraguay]]an Adriana L\u00f3pez.<ref name=\"patenimiento\">[http://www.elpais.com.co/elpais/entretenimiento/noticias/vida-kike-santander-contada-por-sus-seres-cercanos La vida de Kike Santander contada por sus seres m\u00e1s cercanos] (in Spanish: Kike Santander's life told by their loved ones). Posted by Isabel Pelaez, Reporter of newspapers ''[[El Pa\u00eds]]''. Sunday, September 29, 2013. Retrieved November 10, 2013, to 2:16pm.</ref><ref name=\"JYL\" /> The couple have two children: Andrea, Adriana's daughter from a previous relationship; and Alejandro, born to the couple in 2008. In 2004 Santander became a naturalized US citizen,<ref name=\"JYL\" /> and the family settled in [[Huntington Park, California]] in October 2010.\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n\n===''Billboard'' Latin Music Awards===\nSantander has received the following [[Billboard Latin Music Awards|''Billboard'' Latin Music Awards]] and nominations.<ref name=\"LMBA\">''Billboard'' Latin Music Awards:\n\n*'''1999 Awards''': {{cite journal\n|title=10th Annual Billboard Latin Music Conference\n|last=Lannert\n|first=John\n|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=eigEAAAAMBAJ&lpg=PA7&pg=RA1-PA42#v=onepage&q&f=false\n|work=Billboard\n|publisher=Prometheus Global Media\n|volume=111\n|issue=17\n|page=42\n|date=April 24, 1999\n|accessdate=June 29, 2015\n}}\n\n*'''2000 Awards''': {{cite journal\n|title=Catch Some Rising Stars\n|last=Lannert\n|first=John\n|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=EA8EAAAAMBAJ&lpg=PP1&pg=RA1-PA20#v=onepage&q&f=false\n|work=Billboard\n|publisher=Prometheus Global Media\n|volume=112\n|issue=18\n|page=LM-18\n|date=April 29, 2000\n|accessdate=June 29, 2015\n}}\n\n*'''2001 Awards''': {{cite journal\n|title=Billboard Awards Recognizes The Best in Latin Music\n|last=Coco\n|first=Leila\n|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=oxMEAAAAMBAJ&lpg=PA1&pg=PA56#v=onepage&q&f=false\n|work=Billboard\n|publisher=Prometheus Global Media\n|volume=113\n|issue=17\n|page=LM-6\n|date=November 30, 2004\n|accessdate=June 29, 2015\n}}\n\n*'''2004 Awards''': {{cite journal\n|title=2004 Billboard Music Awards\n|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/65464/2004-billboard-music-awards-finalists\n|work=Billboard\n|publisher=Prometheus Global Media\n|date=May 5, 2001\n|accessdate=June 29, 2015\n}}\n\n</ref>\n\n{{awards table}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" scope=\"row\"| 1999\n|rowspan=\"7\" scope=\"row\"| Himself\n|scope=\"row\"|Songwriter of the Year\n| {{won}}\n|-\n|scope=\"row\"| Producer of the Year\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" scope=\"row\"| 2000\n|scope=\"row\"|Songwriter of the Year\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Producer of the Year\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" scope=\"row\"| 2001\n|scope=\"row\"|Songwriter of the Year\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" scope=\"row\"| Producer of the Year\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n|[[2004 Latin Billboard Music Awards|2004]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n{{end}}\n\n===BMI Latin awards===\nSantander has won the following [[Broadcast Music, Inc.|BMI]] awards.<ref name=\"BMI\">BMI Awards:\n\n*'''1997 Awards''': {{cite journal\n|title=Los Premios Latino de BMI\n|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=AQoEAAAAMBAJ&lpg=PA1&pg=PA85#v=onepage&q&f=false\n|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]\n|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]\n|page=85\n|date=September 13, 1997\n|accessdate=June 29, 2015\n}}\n\n*'''1999 Awards''': {{cite journal\n|title=Los Premios Latinos de BMI Latin 1999\n|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=CQ0EAAAAMBAJ&lpg=PA1&pg=RA1-PA33#v=onepage&q&f=false\n|work=Billboard\n|publisher=Prometheus Global Media\n|volume=111\n|issue=26\n|page=33\n|date=June 26, 1999\n|accessdate=June 29, 2015\n}}\n\n*'''2000 Awards''': {{cite web\n|title=BMI Honors Top Latin Writers and Publishers\n|url=http://www.bmi.com/news/entry/20000502_bmi_honors_top_latin_writers_and_publishers\n|publisher=Broadcast Music, Inc.\n|date=May 1, 2000\n|accessdate=June 29, 2015\n}}\n\n*'''2001 Awards''': {{cite journal\n|title=Three Writers Tie For BMI Latin Award\n|last=Pesselnick\n|first=Jill\n|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=BBQEAAAAMBAJ&lpg=PA1&pg=PA9#v=onepage&q&f=false\n|work=Billboard\n|publisher=Prometheus Global Media\n|volume=113\n|issue=18\n|page=9\n|date=May 5, 2001\n|accessdate=June 29, 2015\n}}\n\n*'''2002 Awards''': {{cite web\n|title=2002 BMI Latin Awards: Song List\n|url=http:/